Params: {3: 'The three familiar Constructs soon left after you paid with the coins found in the arcade.'}
{3: 'But no matter how hard you try, you cannot seem to paste the couplets on the door frame. It is already your fifth attempt.'}
{3: 'As you reach to the sticky tape, someone hands it over in advance.'}
{3: 'Lucia stands behind you with shopping bags in her hands.'}
{3: 'The fifth attempt also failed. The tapes completely disappeared before even adhering.'}
{3: 'The last challenge only started when you entered the yard. These couplets probably need to be used at the right location to unlock the corresponding trial.'}
{2: 'Lucia', 3: 'Lee said there were some spices missing and went to the next street alone.', 4: '1'}
{3: "You put the couplets away and bring the ingredients inside the building. After telling Liv about the couplets and Lee's words, three of you wait together for him to return."}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lucia', 3: 'I think I should go find him.', 4: '1'}
{3: 'As they stand up, you hear the familiar knocking sound on the door.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Watanabe (?)', 3: 'This guy was lost. Is he one of yours?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lee', 3: 'I just happened to be there by coincidence.', 4: '2'}
{2: 'Watanabe (?)', 3: 'Just happened to walk to the city border? There is no road over there.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Patrol', 3: 'You\'ve got the wrong person. I am "Patrol".', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Patrol', 3: "But I don't blame you. I seldom show up in front of people.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Patrol', 3: "Anyway, I've got to go. Don't let him go out alone next time.", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Liv', 3: "Lee must be tired after all that walking. I'll do it.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lee', 3: 'Can we really leave this to Lucia?', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lucia', 3: 'I will take care of the dinner.', 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lucia', 3: "Commandant, you can take a rest in the living room. The kitchen can't fit so many of us.", 4: '1'}
{3: 'Since Lucia has already said so, you can only let her do it. Before two of them enter the kitchen, you cannot help but open your mouth again—'}
{2: 'Lucia', 3: "I won't put too many spices like last time.", 4: '1'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Liv', 3: 'I will do my best to help Lucia.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'I should have some faith in them.', 3: '81'}
{3: 'Right after your words, a loud explosion comes from the kitchen.'}
